fident that the current contractors and other possible new ones that you are talking about are equally signed up to delivering that on the initial, original timetable by end 2017?  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Mike Penning</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: Yes, because, one, we would not bring a contractor in that could not give us that commitment.  I am now seeking</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—and there are</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> very detailed negotiations going on with some of our existing providers</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—an assurance that they can do that.  That is very important.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q63 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Stephen Lloyd:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> Can I ask that the Department</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">occasionally, it did not do this as well as I think it could have done</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">—</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">put in some definite penalty clauses, then, within the contracts for this delivery?  I am delighted that you are confident that it will be still be by end 2017—fingers crossed—but I would be very concerned to discover, a year or so down the line, that there is slippage on that, perhaps because the contractors cannot cope.  Are there any thoughts within the </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Department </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">of inserting penalty clauses on those agreements?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Mike Penning</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: There are penalty clauses now, with both of the providers, Capita and </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Atos</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">.  The </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Department </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">is very much taking that forward where they may be in breach of contract.  There are penalty causes in there, and they are very severe.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Q64 </span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Stephen Lloyd:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> For the timetables up to 2017?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Mike Penning</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">: Yes.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Chair:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> We have some more questions on contracts that will be coming up.  Sheila, you wanted to come in?  </span></p><p style="mar